        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31820",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=robinsk",
                        "name": "robinsk",
                        "displayName": "Robin Skoglund",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "So you want a boolean switch in the menu helper for enabling this behaviour (using page CSS classes for LI instead of A)?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=robinsk",
                        "name": "robinsk",
                        "displayName": "Robin Skoglund",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-13T04:26:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-13T04:26:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31830",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=syncer",
                        "name": "syncer",
                        "displayName": "Mina R Waheeb",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There is no need to style the A element because you can easy style it by CSS2 selectors (.class a) which currently implement in all the browsers but for backward compatible it would be suitable. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=syncer",
                        "name": "syncer",
                        "displayName": "Mina R Waheeb",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-13T10:29:16.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-13T10:29:16.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35414",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=robinsk",
                        "name": "robinsk",
                        "displayName": "Robin Skoglund",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree.\r\n\r\nThe only thing that bites me is that I remember there was a reason for styling the A (instead of the LI). That is to say, there was a reason for that design choice, but I can't remember it right now. Will look further into it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=robinsk",
                        "name": "robinsk",
                        "displayName": "Robin Skoglund",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-20T02:25:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-20T02:25:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35416",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=software@wemb.info",
                        "name": "software@wemb.info",
                        "displayName": "Wouter E. M. Berben",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "If you are wondering: I've modified the Zend_View_Helper_Navigation_Menu so it sets the class on the list item element and not the anchor element. It works and doesn't show any defects. For me this isn't any issue, but I would prefer to see the sollution in the original Framework. Thanks.\r\n\r\nI believe the design reason is absolute since CSS2.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=software@wemb.info",
                        "name": "software@wemb.info",
                        "displayName": "Wouter E. M. Berben",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-20T02:59:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-20T02:59:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35418",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=software@wemb.info",
                        "name": "software@wemb.info",
                        "displayName": "Wouter E. M. Berben",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I mean absolete, not absolute :) Sorry for that.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=software@wemb.info",
                        "name": "software@wemb.info",
                        "displayName": "Wouter E. M. Berben",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-20T03:17:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-20T03:17:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36729",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stephane",
                        "name": "stephane",
                        "displayName": "St\u00e9phane",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This would be a nice improvement indeed. Did you have the time to look into it Robin?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stephane",
                        "name": "stephane",
                        "displayName": "St\u00e9phane",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-05T03:16:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-05T03:16:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38007",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=svestka",
                        "name": "svestka",
                        "displayName": "Peter Slivka",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've created a small patch for this. Maybe it helps someone, it just use the same class names for LI elements as for the anchors.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=svestka",
                        "name": "svestka",
                        "displayName": "Peter Slivka",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-25T06:23:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-25T06:23:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40451",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stephane",
                        "name": "stephane",
                        "displayName": "St\u00e9phane",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Robin, would it be possible to integrate the patch from Peter? Regarding CSS, we are able to [target a child element from a given element|http:\/\/reference.sitepoint.com\/css\/childselector]:\r\n\r\n{code:xml} \r\nLI.active A {\r\n  \/* my rules *\/\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nbut not the opposite. At least, would it be possible to have an update on this issue?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stephane",
                        "name": "stephane",
                        "displayName": "St\u00e9phane",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-12T10:21:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-12T10:21:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45821",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "For backward compatibility in the HTML output we need (for the moment) a boolean switch.\r\nIn Version 2 we remove the switch and set the class to the list element. We also improve the whole rendering for all helpers and all elements (ul, li, a, span, \u2026).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-04-06T09:05:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-04-06T09:05:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47026",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I have written some tests and the implementation.\r\nFor the current major release, there will be a boolean switch.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
